00:40:33,180 --> 00:40:34,980
 I'll just stare at you, okay?

771
00:40:34,980 --> 00:40:38,780
 Here's what I want you to do.

772
00:40:38,780 --> 00:40:41,780
 I want you to imagine standing in heaven

773
00:40:41,780 --> 00:40:44,460
 before the throne of God, worshiping Jesus.

774
00:40:44,460 --> 00:40:45,900
 Just imagine this.

775
00:40:45,900 --> 00:40:48,260
 Imagine you're worshiping Jesus.

776
00:40:48,260 --> 00:40:49,840
 There's fullness of joy.

777
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:54,440
 And imagine looking to your right and your left,

778
00:40:54,440 --> 00:40:58,860
 and you see your good friends who also loved Jesus.

779
00:40:58,860 --> 00:41:00,780
 You see your family who loved Jesus,

780
00:41:00,780 --> 00:41:02,620
 and they're worshiping Jesus as well.

781
00:41:02,620 --> 00:41:03,460
 Now,

782
00:41:03,460 --> 00:41:10,740
 is there any brother or sister in the faith

783
00:41:10,740 --> 00:41:16,660
 that you could see in heaven?

784
00:41:16,660 --> 00:41:20,620
 And you'd feel this awkwardness,

785
00:41:20,620 --> 00:41:23,520
 like there's something unresolved between the two of you.

786
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:27,480
 Like imagine how out of place that awkwardness

787
00:41:27,480 --> 00:41:31,900
 between the two of you would be standing before Jesus,

788
00:41:31,900 --> 00:41:39,920
 experiencing the fullest extent of His grace and forgiveness.

789
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:43,360
 Is there anyone that comes to mind?

790
00:41:43,360 --> 00:41:48,800
 Let me encourage you to open your eyes.

791
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:50,400
 Hey, don't wait.

792
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:52,700
 Don't wait for heaven to resolve something.

793
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:55,320
 Love one another.

794
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:57,800
 Romans 12, 18 says, "If possible,

795
00:41:57,800 --> 00:42:02,520
 "so far as it depends on you, live peacefully with all."

796
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:05,000
 Just wanna invite everyone real quick to just say,

797
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:08,300
 say these words, "Will you forgive me?"

798
00:42:08,300 --> 00:42:12,440
 And then say, "I forgive you."

799
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:15,840
 Look, if those words never come out of your mouth,

800
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:18,360
 you're a very difficult Christian friend.

801
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:22,000
 Look, we're sinful people.

802
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,160
 We're gonna hurt one another.

803
00:42:23,160 --> 00:42:24,520
 We should forgive each other.

804
00:42:24,520 --> 00:42:25,360
 Why?

805
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:27,920
 Because we know what it's like to be forgiven.

806
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:30,360
 If we refuse to forgive, it's as if we're saying,

807
00:42:30,360 --> 00:42:32,960
 "Jesus, I can see why you would forgive me,

808
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:34,860
 "but don't expect me to forgive them.

809
00:42:34,860 --> 00:42:37,800
 "I deserve to be forgiven by you.

810
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:39,720
 "They don't deserve to be forgiven by me."

811
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:41,040
 That makes no sense.

812
00:42:41,040 --> 00:42:44,240
 And finally, look, I'm out of time,

813
00:42:44,240 --> 00:42:48,620
 but let me just encourage you to serve like the end is near.

814
00:42:48,620 --> 00:42:50,220
 Serve like the end is near.

815
00:42:50,220 --> 00:42:52,800
 Peter finishes up and says,

816
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:56,120
 "Show hospitality to one another without grumbling.

817
00:42:56,120 --> 00:42:57,700
 "As each has received a gift,

818
00:42:57,700 --> 00:42:59,020
 "use it to serve one another

819
00:42:59,020 --> 00:43:01,000
 "as good stewards of God's varied grace.

820
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:03,580
 "Whoever speaks is one who speaks oracles of God.

821
00:43:03,580 --> 00:43:05,180
 "Whoever serves is one who serves

822
00:43:05,180 --> 00:43:06,940
 "by the strength that God supplies,

823
00:43:06,940 --> 00:43:08,520
 "in order that in everything,

824
00:43:08,520 --> 00:43:10,960
 "God may be glorified through Jesus Christ.

825
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:15,960
 "To him belong glory and dominion forever and ever, amen."

826
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:18,120
 What's the point?

827
00:43:18,120 --> 00:43:21,200
 Peter's just saying, "Look, if you know Jesus Christ,

828
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:23,840
 "God has actually given you a supernatural gift.

829
00:43:23,840 --> 00:43:27,900
 "You have been wired by God in some supernatural way

830
00:43:27,900 --> 00:43:30,700
 "to actually serve his church."

831
00:43:30,700 --> 00:43:33,880
 So let me just encourage you.

832
00:43:33,880 --> 00:43:37,900
 Look, you don't have to come to Watermark for church,

833
00:43:37,900 --> 00:43:42,400
 but you should belong to some church.

834
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:43,800
 And I'm not just talking about

835
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:45,440
 showing up sometimes on Sundays.

836
00:43:45,440 --> 00:43:50,440
 I'm talking about being an integral part of the church.

837
00:43:50,880 --> 00:43:55,240
 God has wired you with a gift to serve the church.

838
00:43:55,240 --> 00:43:56,840
 It's been given to you by his spirit

839
00:43:56,840 --> 00:43:58,920
 and it's given to serve the body.

840
00:43:58,920 --> 00:44:00,480
 I went to Texas A&M University

841
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:01,520
 and there was a saying around there,

842
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:03,320
 like, "Don't be a two-percenter."

843
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,200
 What's the point?

844
00:44:04,200 --> 00:44:05,600
 Like, be all in.

845
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:08,440
 Don't just do the bare minimum.

846
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:12,960
 God has wired you with gifts to belong to his family.

847
00:44:12,960 --> 00:44:14,000
 That's what the church is,

848
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:16,760
 is it's a family where we come together

849
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:18,200
 and we serve together.

850
00:44:18,200 --> 00:44:21,320
 Look, here's what's happening at Watermark.

851
00:44:21,320 --> 00:44:23,100
 At Watermark, it's young adults

852
00:44:23,100 --> 00:44:24,640
 that are leading the way in worship

853
00:44:24,640 --> 00:44:26,720
 in this room on Sundays.

854
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:27,740
 It's incredible.

855
00:44:27,740 --> 00:44:31,760
 It's been young men in their 20s

856
00:44:31,760 --> 00:44:35,240
 that have invested in my son's lives.

857
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:36,960
 And I'm so grateful for it.

858
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:39,600
 Look, you can play an instrumental role

859
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:40,840
 in the next generation,

860
00:44:40,840 --> 00:44:42,200
 some high school students' lives,

861
00:44:42,200 --> 00:44:43,160
 middle school students,

862
00:44:43,160 --> 00:44:45,640
 little kids, like God can use you

863
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:49,120
 to bring people to faith by the power of the Spirit.

864
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:51,340
 Leverage your life in the church

865
00:44:51,340 --> 00:44:53,240
 for the sake of the gospel.

866
00:44:53,240 --> 00:44:56,980
 Serve like the end is near.

867
00:44:56,980 --> 00:45:00,480
 Go all in with Jesus,

868
00:45:00,480 --> 00:45:04,260
 endure opposition, pray, love,

869
00:45:04,260 --> 00:45:06,120
 and serve like the end is near.

870
00:45:06,120 --> 00:45:08,880
 Just go back to where I started

871
00:45:08,880 --> 00:45:10,640
 with that race analogy.

872
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:11,840
 Some of you guys might feel like

873
00:45:11,840 --> 00:45:14,280
 you're in your first mile with Jesus,

874
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:15,360
 where it's just exciting.

875
00:45:15,360 --> 00:45:17,760
 You just became a Christian recently,

876
00:45:17,760 --> 00:45:19,400
 and that's awesome.

877
00:45:19,400 --> 00:45:20,460
 Some of y'all might feel like

878
00:45:20,460 --> 00:45:22,360
 you're in your second mile,

879
00:45:22,360 --> 00:45:23,200
 where you're like,

880
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:25,560
 "Sometimes I wonder why I chose to follow Jesus,

881
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:27,680
 "because it's hard.

882
00:45:27,680 --> 00:45:29,940
 "It's just not going like I thought it would,

883
00:45:29,940 --> 00:45:32,800
 "and I'm thinking about quitting."

884
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:35,560
 But I'm just telling you,

885
00:45:35,560 --> 00:45:37,040
 if you know Jesus,

886
00:45:37,040 --> 00:45:41,240
 you're actually in the third mile.

887
00:45:41,240 --> 00:45:43,600
 Keep going.

888
00:45:43,600 --> 00:45:45,160
 Keep going.

889
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:46,760
 The finish line is ahead.

890
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:49,160
 Run your race, pump your arms,

891
00:45:49,160 --> 00:45:51,480
 lift your knees, widen your stride.

892
00:45:51,480 --> 00:45:52,800
 Christ is coming back.

893
00:45:52,800 --> 00:45:54,200
 It might not be today.

894
00:45:54,200 --> 00:45:55,840
 It might not be tomorrow.

895
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:57,760
 It could be.

896
00:45:57,760 --> 00:46:00,520
 But don't live like Jesus is coming back one day.

897
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:03,140
 Live like he can come back any day.

898
00:46:03,140 --> 00:46:05,240
 And maybe you're here

899
00:46:05,240 --> 00:46:07,160
 and you've never started the race with Jesus.

900
00:46:07,160 --> 00:46:09,160
 You've never put your trust in him.

901
00:46:09,160 --> 00:46:12,440
 Look, Jesus Christ left heaven,

902
00:46:12,440 --> 00:46:14,380
 came to earth, lived perfectly.

903
00:46:14,380 --> 00:46:15,220
 Why?

904
00:46:15,220 --> 00:46:16,520
 Because you and I couldn't live perfectly.

905
00:46:16,520 --> 00:46:18,000
 He died sacrificially.

906
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:18,840
 Why?

907
00:46:18,840 --> 00:46:20,760
 So that you and I wouldn't have to be punished

908
00:46:20,760 --> 00:46:23,160
 for all of the ways that we wronged God.

909
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:26,080
 And then Jesus Christ rose from the dead victoriously.

910
00:46:26,080 --> 00:46:27,360
 Why?

911
00:46:27,360 --> 00:46:30,560
 So that you and I could be raised to a new life with God

912
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:33,000
 that begins the day you believe in Jesus

913
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:35,020
 and lasts for all of eternity.

914
00:46:35,020 --> 00:46:38,520
 If you wanna begin the race with Jesus,

915
00:46:38,520 --> 00:46:40,760
 all you have to do is call out to him in prayer

916
00:46:40,760 --> 00:46:42,320
 and invite him into your life.

917
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:43,520
 Let's pray together now.

918
00:46:44,260 --> 00:46:46,840
 (gentle music)

919
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:49,740
 And if that's you,

920
00:46:49,740 --> 00:46:51,660
 if you wanna begin a relationship with Jesus,

921
00:46:51,660 --> 00:46:53,780
 I'd even encourage you right now to just say,

922
00:46:53,780 --> 00:46:56,660
 Lord Jesus, would you come into my life tonight?

923
00:46:56,660 --> 00:47:02,700
 Thank you that you died on the cross for me.

924
00:47:02,700 --> 00:47:08,800
 Thank you that you rose from the dead for me.

925
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:13,380
 Would you come into my life?

926
00:47:14,120 --> 00:47:16,600
 Would you forgive me of my sins?

927
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:21,600
 And would you lead me in a new life?

928
00:47:21,600 --> 00:47:30,760
 And then whether you just put your trust in Jesus

929
00:47:30,760 --> 00:47:35,760
 or maybe you've known Jesus for a long time.

930
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:38,120
 I don't know who it was in this room,

931
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:39,800
 but right at the end of worship,

932
00:47:39,800 --> 00:47:43,000
 David was just talking about saying yes to Jesus.

933
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,920
 And someone just called out yes, Jesus.

934
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:46,720
 And I was so moved by that.

935
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:49,840
 And I just wonder,

936
00:47:49,840 --> 00:47:55,960
 like maybe that's your simple offering to God tonight.

937
00:47:55,960 --> 00:48:01,220
 As we sing, even to just say, yes, Jesus,

938
00:48:01,220 --> 00:48:03,780
 like my yes is on the table to you.

939
00:48:03,780 --> 00:48:08,240
 I wanna be all in with you.

940
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:10,840
 I wanna endure opposition for you.

941
00:48:10,840 --> 00:48:13,240
 I wanna pray fervently to you.

942
00:48:13,240 --> 00:48:15,720
 I wanna love well for you.

943
00:48:15,720 --> 00:48:17,920
 I wanna serve the church for you.

944
00:48:17,920 --> 00:48:20,420
 Yes, yes, Jesus.

945
00:48:20,420 --> 00:48:22,920
 Lord, we love you.

946
00:48:22,920 --> 00:48:25,200
 You're worthy of our yes.

947
00:48:25,200 --> 00:48:26,880
 You're worthy of our lives.

948
00:48:26,880 --> 00:48:29,100
 You can have everything.

949
00:48:29,100 --> 00:48:33,280
 Use us for your glory in Jesus' name.

950
00:48:33,280 --> 00:48:35,920
 Amen.

